<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I see the roll as a way to ensure the wait could continue without contention, to stall, essentially. Maybe I'm wrong.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You are wrong, and I resent the implication that we needed some device to &quot;stall&quot; in order to kill something like Ragefire.  Talk to me in game if you would like a list of the numerous baddies we have keeled spur of the moment with little or no problem whatsoever.<br>
<br>
As for the real reason why I proposed a roll, well if you don't understand it by now no amount of explaining is going to make it clear.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> But most of the people that hate &quot;the race&quot; usually toss up Uberguilds as the reason they hate it, because they can't &quot;beat them in a race&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
